(2331, 1, '2014-12-18 10:59:25', '2014-12-18 10:59:25', '[two_third]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<h1><strong>Message from the Mayor</strong></h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe debate over the juxtaposition of population issue and poverty may be almost as old as population itself and, in the view of the increasing trend tow­ards its complete regulation. Not surprisingly, and is generally recognized by contemporary writers on this topic, the philosophical and moral arguments for or against population issue/s have remained remarkably unchanged since the beginning of the debate.\r\n\r\n“For the most part of the past century, the Philippine economy performed poorly, especially against the backdrop of the dynamic East Asian economies. Spurts of growth were often followed by bust and stagnation. Not surprisingly absolute poverty among a significant proportion of the population has persisted. The country’s real per capita GDP at the turn of the 21<sup>st</sup> century was just about the same as that in the early 1980s, which\r\n\r\nThe debate over the juxtaposition of population issue and poverty may be almost as old as population itself and, in the view of the increasing trend tow­ards its complete regulation. Not surprisingly, and is generally recognized by contemporary writers on this topic, the philosophical and moral arguments for or against population issue/s have remained remarkably unchanged since the beginning of the debate.\r\n\r\n[/two_third]\r\n[one_third]<img src="http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/mayor.png" alt="mayorprofile" />[/one_third]', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-18 10:59:25', '2014-12-18 10:59:25', '', 5, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=2331', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
